            , Esq. sworn.</p>
               <p>Between one and two, the 8th of October, I was crossing from <placeName id="t17901027-47-crimeloc253">Cornhill</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17901027-47-crimeloc253" type="placeName" value="Cornhill"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17901027-47-crimeloc253" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17901027-47-off250 t17901027-47-crimeloc253"></join> to go into Lombard-street, in the narrow alley that goes into Change-alley, I felt some thing at my pocket; I immediately put my hand to my pocket, and my handkerchief was gone; I turned round, and seized the prisoner, and said, you have picked my pocket; on searching the prisoner, I found a handkerchief concealed upon him, which I knew to be mine; I have kept it ever since; it is a linen handkerchief; the prisoner begged I would forgive him.</p>
               <p>PRISONER's DEFENCE.</p>
               <p>I was going up a narrow passage, and saw the handkerchief laying on the ground, and took it up; the gentleman said, I had his handkerchief: I said, I had not.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17901027-47-verdict254" type="verdictDescription">
                     <interp inst="t17901027-47-verdict254" type="verdictCategory" value="guilty"></interp>
               GUILTY
            </rs>.</p>
               <p>
                  <rs id="t17901027-47-punish255" type="punishmentDescription">
